<!-- ================= THE GAP ================= -->
<section class="chro-grey">
  <div class="chro-wrap chro-sec">
    <div class="chro-max720">
      <div class="chro-eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:16px;">The clarity gap</div>
      <h2 class="chro-h2">Your org chart is a picture. It doesn't know what anyone does.</h2>
      <p class="chro-body" style="margin-top:18px;max-width:44rem;">A box with a name and a title tells you who reports to whom &mdash; not who owns which number, who's thriving versus coasting, or where the work actually sits. The most important asset you steward is the one you can see the least clearly.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="chro-grid3 reveal">
      <div class="chro-card">
        <span class="chro-chip" style="background:rgba(220,38,38,.1);"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#dc2626" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><rect x="4" y="4" width="16" height="16" rx="2" stroke-dasharray="3 3"/></svg></span>
        <h3>Roles are fuzzy</h3>
        <p>A title isn't a role. Without a clear owner and a number per seat, accountability blurs &mdash; the same work gets done twice, or falls through the cracks, and no one's quite sure whose it was.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="chro-card">
        <span class="chro-chip" style="background:rgba(217,119,6,.12);"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#d97706" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M3 3v18h18"/><path d="M7 14l4-4 3 3 5-6"/></svg></span>
        <h3>Activity hides contribution</h3>
        <p>You can see who's busy. You can't easily see who's moving the business. Reviews end up running on impressions and recency, not on what each person actually owned and delivered.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="chro-card">
        <span class="chro-chip" style="background:rgba(13,125,242,.1);"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#0d7df2" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><circle cx="9" cy="8" r="3"/><path d="M3 20c0-3.3 2.7-6 6-6s6 2.7 6 6"/><rect x="16" y="5" width="6" height="6" rx="2"/></svg></span>
        <h3>The workforce is going hybrid</h3>
        <p>Your people are bringing on agents that do real work. Your headcount plan, your chart, and your reviews still only count humans &mdash; so half the future workforce isn't anywhere in your system.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ================= ONE OPERATING SYSTEM ================= -->
<section class="chro-paper">
  <div class="chro-wrap chro-sec">
    <div class="chro-max720">
      <div class="chro-eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:16px;">One operating system</div>
      <h2 class="chro-h2">An accountability chart that knows what every seat actually owns.</h2>
      <p class="chro-body" style="margin-top:18px;max-width:44rem;">OTP turns the org chart from a picture into the source of truth. Every seat &mdash; person or agent &mdash; carries the role it owns, the SOPs behind it, who it reports to, and the number it's measured on. The people decisions you make every week finally have data underneath them.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="chro-grid2 reveal">
      <div class="chro-card">
        <h3>Every seat, clearly owned</h3>
        <p>Roles, responsibilities, and the one number each seat is accountable for &mdash; defined and visible. No more guessing who owns what, or discovering a gap only when something is dropped.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="chro-card">
        <h3>Right people, right seats</h3>
        <p>See where someone's in the wrong seat, where a seat has no owner, and where the work has outgrown the role. The hardest people calls become evidence-based, not gut-based.</p>
