</section>

<!-- ================= THE NEW LAYER (light editorial statement) ================= -->
<section class="chro-quoteband">
  <div class="chro-wrap chro-sec chro-center" style="max-width:880px;">
    <div class="chro-eyebrow" style="justify-content:center;margin-bottom:20px;">Not a better tool &mdash; a new layer</div>
    <span class="chro-qmark">&ldquo;</span>
    <p class="chro-quote" style="margin:6px auto 0;max-width:25ch;">It's not a better HRIS. It's the org chart that finally knows what everyone &mdash; and every agent &mdash; actually <span class="accent">does</span>.</p>
    <p class="chro-body" style="max-width:44rem;margin:22px auto 0;">HR systems were built to store people records. The org of the next decade is people <em>and</em> agents doing measurable work side by side &mdash; and nothing on your stack was built to design, staff, or grow it. OTP isn't software-as-a-service. It's data-as-a-service for the workforce you're about to lead.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ================= MULTI-ENTITY ================= -->
<section class="chro-paper">
  <div class="chro-wrap chro-sec">
    <div class="chro-max720">
      <div class="chro-eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:16px;">For multi-entity people teams</div>
      <h2 class="chro-h2">Standardize how every company is built &mdash; and find the ones that aren't.</h2>
